    <edge source=" that soaked into the hot &quot;bread&quot; with a&#10; genuinely dairy smell. &quot;Splendid, Bailey,&quot; I said.&#10; &#10; &quot;We are not amused,&quot; said Captain Winkelmann, accepting a second&#10; helping of the pseudo-turkey. &quot;You are improving, Belly-Robber, but&#10; only arithmetically. Your first efforts were so hideous as to require&#10; a geometric progression of improving excellence to raise them to mere&#10; edibility. By the time we are halfway 'round the Sun, I trust you will&#10; have learned to cook with the competence of a freshman Home Economics&#10; student. That will be all, Bailey.&quot;&#10; &#10; The crew and my fellow-officers were amused by Winkelmann's riding of&#10; Bailey; they were in addition gratified that the battle between their&#10; Captain and their Cook served to feed them so well. Most spacers embark&#10; on an outward voyage somewhat plump, having eaten enough on their last&#10; few days aground to smuggle several hundred calories of fat and many&#10; memories of good food aboard with them. This trip, none of the men had&#10; lost weight during the first four months in space. Winkelmann, indeed,&#10; seemed to have gained. His uniform" target="Captain Winkelmann treats Bailey harshly and sets high expectations for him because he wants Bailey to find a way to produce good food using Chlorella tanks during their journey to Mars. The Captain believes that Bailey has the ability to improve his culinary skills, even when starting with unappetizing ingredients like Chlorella. This harsh treatment is intended to motivate Bailey to experiment, improvise, and widen his horizons of ingenuity, hoping that he will eventually learn to create edible and enjoyable meals from the algae-based food source.&#10;&#10;The Captain's primary concern is their journey to Mars, and ensuring that the crew remains well-fed throughout the trip. The harsh treatment is a means to an end – achieving a reliable and tasty food source for his crew, despite the challenging circumstances of space travel. By pushing Bailey to his limits, Winkelmann ultimately improves morale on the ship, as the crew enjoys better meals and remains healthier during their long journey.">
