    <edge source="&#10;&#10; &#10; &quot;Doc, do you like Winkelmann?&quot; the Cook asked me.&#10; &#10; &quot;Not much,&quot; I said. &quot;I suspect that the finest gift our Captain can&#10; give his mother is to be absent from her on Mother's Day. But we've got&#10; to live with him. He's a good man at driving a ship.&quot;&#10; &#10; &quot;I wish he'd leave off driving this Cook,&quot; Bailey said. &quot;The fat swine!&quot;&#10; &#10; &quot;His plumpness is an unwitting tribute to your cooking, Bailey,&quot; I&#10; said. &quot;He eats well. We all do. I've dined aboard a lot of spacers in&#10; my time, and I'll testify that you set a table second to none.&quot;&#10; &#10; Bailey took a handful of dried Chlorella from a bin and fingered it. It&#10; was green, smelled of swamp, and looked appetizing as a bedsore. &quot;This&#10; is what I have to work with,&quot; he said. He tossed the stuff back into&#10; its bin. &quot;In Ohio, which is my home country, in the presence of ladies,&#10; we'd call such garbage Horse-Leavings.&quot;&#10; &#10; &quot;You'll never make Winkelmann" target="The Ship's Cook plays a crucial role in the morale and well-being of the crew on a spacer, as demonstrated by historical examples such as the H.M.S. Ajax fiasco and the Benjo Maru incident. By transforming offal into edible meals, the Ship's Cook performs a daily miracle that can significantly impact the mental state of the crew. Good cooking can boost morale, while poor cooking can lead to discontent, mutiny, or even poisoning.&#10;&#10;In the case of the H.M.S. Ajax fiasco, a galleyman's negligence in handling heavy water from the ship's shielding contaminated Chlorella tanks, leading to deuterium poisoning among the crew members. This incident highlights the importance of proper food preparation and storage on a spacer.&#10;&#10;The Benjo Maru incident involved a Ship's Cook allowing algae-based staff-of-life to become contaminated with a fast-growing Saccharomycodes yeast, causing every man aboard to consume an alcoholic substance that fermented each bite they ate into sake. This example shows how a minor mistake in food preparation can have severe consequences for the entire crew.&#10;&#10;Therefore, the Ship's Cook wields significant power over the well-being and morale of the crew on a spacer, making their role indispensable to the success of any mission.">
