arge groups of people on spaceships and highlighted the adaptability and resilience required to survive in harsh environments. The crew's cooking skills improved significantly throughout their journey, as evidenced by their steady weight maintenance and positive feedback from fellow officers. Bailey, the Ship's Cook, even managed to create a meat substitute and dessert using algae, which was well-received by the officers and crew members.&#10;&#10;Therefore, while there was a decline in food quality during the transition from sea to space travel, space explorers had to adapt to new dietary habits and challenges that pushed the boundaries of what was considered edible. Despite these challenges, the crew's cooking skills improved significantly, ensuring their nutritional needs were met throughout the journey.">
